# Tmux Pane Architecture (Design Spec)

> **Status**: Design document for a proposed multi-pane tmux architecture. This describes a system to be built, not current functionality.
>
> **Last Updated**: 2026-03-20
> **Status**: ⚠️ *Planning Phase — Not Implemented*

## Overview

A proposed tmux-based architecture for multi-bot collaboration, where each Telegram topic maps to a tmux window with three role-based panes (Planner | Executor | Reviewer).

## Current Reality vs. This Design

| This Document | Current Codebase Reality |
|--------------|--------------------------|
| 3-pane layout (Planner \| Executor \| Reviewer) | Single pane per session |
| `TmuxWindow`, `TmuxPane` types | Uses `SessionInfo` in `config.Sessions` |
| `PostResponse` hook for @mention routing | Hook doesn't exist in Claude Code |
| `bot_tokens`, `bot_usernames` config fields | Single `BotToken` field; usernames read from Telegram at runtime |
| `MessageRouter` with `routeUpdate()` | Monolithic `listen()` function in `commands.go` |
| `/new`, `/worktree` create 3-pane windows | Create single-pane sessions |

## Hierarchy Mapping

```
Telegram                   Tmux
─────────────────────────────────────────
Group                      Session (ccc)
└── Topic                  └── Window (topic name)
    └── Planner role          └── Pane 0 (left)
    └── Executor role         └── Pane 1 (middle)
    └── Reviewer role         └── Pane 2 (right)
```

